\ul\b\f1\fs36 1. WHEN CLICKS X \f0 BUTTON ON TOP RIGHT\ulnone\b0\fs24\par
If Rich text box is empty, than when closing text editor wont display: "Do you wish to save changes with this text?"\par
\par
If Rich Text Box is present with some text and has not been saved to a file (text file doesn't exists), show that "Do you wish to save changes to this text"?. \par
     \b User clicks Yes -> Save As Dialog Open -> User Saves -> Application Close \par
    User clicks No -> Don't Save the text -> Application Close\par
    User clicks Cancel -> Go back to the application or screen where text present\par
\par
\b0\i\fs34 AND\i0\fs24\par
\par
If Rich Tex Box is present with text and the latest changes has been saved to a current existing file, when user close the text editor screen, application will close and stop running.\par
\par
If Rich Tex Box is present with text and the latest changes has not yet been saved to a current existing file, it will prompt the user with MessageBox "Do you want to save changes to the \{currentFile\}" which if\par
         \b User clicks Yes -> Save the file -> Application Close\par
         User clicks No -> Don't Save the File -> Application Close\par
         User clicks Cancel -> Go back to the application or screen\par
\b0\par
\par
